Program: Outlook
Title: 06/06/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gzd8z
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 7 Jun 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Rob Hamill, a New Zealand Olympic rower talks to Lucy Ash about seeking justice for his brother Kerry, who was murdered by the Khmer Rouge. Rob went to the war crimes tribunal in Cambodia accompanied by a film crew. They recorded the trial and Rob's personal journey of discovery into how and where his brother died. The film, due out next month, is called Brother Number One - that was the name given to Comrade Duch by the Khmer Rouge. Show less